{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/blog/gsoc-2019-an-overview","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>It‚Äôs that time of the year again - Google Summer of Code (GSOC) is ahead of us.\nFor the 4th year running we welcome students to become part of our community and join efforts with mentors and other contributors to make Terasology even more awesome!\nThis year we also have a personal first: We are listed as ‚ÄúThe Terasology Foundation‚Äù!</p>\n<p>But what is <a href=\"https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/\">GSOC</a>?\nIt is a 3-month program sponsored by Google that motivates students from all over the world to join open-source organizations and thrive on real-world software development challenges.\nOrganizations and students find and interact with each other directly and on a social and community-driven basis.</p>\n<p>This year we welcome 9 students to work with us on <a href=\"https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/organizations/4777549354237952/\">various topics</a>, ranging from content and game modes over user experience to under-the-hood technologies.</p>\n<p>Without further ado, let‚Äôs jump right in - and may the 4th year of GSoC be with you. üññ</p>\n<h1 id=\"game-modes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#game-modes\" aria-label=\"game modes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Game Modes</h1>\n<p>Terasology itself is only the bare-bone engine that lies underneath all the amazing modules that our contributors build.\nGame modes bundle these modules together enabling players to immerse themselves into different worlds - be it a classic Craft‚Äôn‚ÄôSurvive scenario or an adventurous puzzle.</p>\n<h2 id=\"light-and-shadow-by-darshan3\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#light-and-shadow-by-darshan3\" aria-label=\"light and shadow by darshan3 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Light And Shadow by <em>darshan3</em></h2>\n<p>The idea for the <a href=\"http://forum.terasology.org/threads/las-light-and-shadow-art-discussion.762/\">Light and Shadow</a> game mode dates back to 2013 when SuperSnark came up with neat artworks backed by elaborate lore of quarreling factions and way too many ideas for a single person to implement.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 446px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 108.85416666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/3e828/las_red-keep.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/e6f2f/las_red-keep.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/5021b/las_red-keep.webp 446w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 446px) 100vw, 446px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/8514f/las_red-keep.png 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/804b2/las_red-keep.png 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/6244b/las_red-keep.png 446w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 446px) 100vw, 446px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/ModuleSite/static/42ce5c05cf6ff6c89edd8ac1df5ca574/6244b/las_red-keep.png\"\n            alt=\"LightAndShadow\"\n            title=\"LightAndShadow\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p>We are happy that <em>darshan3</em> takes on the task to develop this idea into a fast-paced Capture-the-Flag mode set in a fantasy world.\nHe can build on present board-game-like model designs and animations provided by glasz and others, such as poker chip trees and fighting chess pieces.\nAt the end of the summer, the existing features will be expanded by team balancing, automated respawn and round restart, as well as new equipment for attack and defense.</p>\n<h2 id=\"metal-renegades\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#metal-renegades\" aria-label=\"metal renegades permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Metal Renegades</h2>\n<p>Metal Renegades is another brilliant idea born out of the imagination of our Lore Master SuperSnark.\nSet in a futuristic and steampunky western world populated by robots, another faction conflict arises.\nBy gathering resources, building mechanical systems and interacting with NPCs, the player can influence this open world.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.895833333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/3e828/mr_good-bad-gooey.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/e6f2f/mr_good-bad-gooey.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/8b983/mr_good-bad-gooey.webp 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/b2d4b/mr_good-bad-gooey.webp 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/bfc0a/mr_good-bad-gooey.webp 1326w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/8514f/mr_good-bad-gooey.png 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/804b2/mr_good-bad-gooey.png 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/e5715/mr_good-bad-gooey.png 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/4ad3a/mr_good-bad-gooey.png 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/c2d9c/mr_good-bad-gooey.png 1326w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/ModuleSite/static/6cd67441e9bd9ee4eac5e0a56ce88a79/e5715/mr_good-bad-gooey.png\"\n            alt=\"MetalRenegades\"\n            title=\"MetalRenegades\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p><em>AndyTechGuy</em> will make this idea come to life in an initial world implementation including <a href=\"https://trello.com/c/HySvX0oY/106-andytechguy-metal-renegades-world\">basic world</a> generation with settlements and outposts themed to this setting.\nAnother deliverable will be NPCs and their interaction with the player.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://trello.com/c/ai7v5Q16/107-wabadump-metal-renegades-multiplayer\">interaction of players</a> among themselves will be brought in by <em>Mayant Mukul</em> including game mechanics for fighting, hunting and looting.\nThe player will furthermore be enabled to sell or trade gathered items.</p>\n<h1 id=\"content\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#content\" aria-label=\"content permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Content</h1>\n<p>Full-fledged game modes depend on content modules delivering specific mechanisms or themes.\nThese building blocks are essential to our open, modularized framework.</p>\n<h2 id=\"apiculture-by-cameron-mcwilliams\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#apiculture-by-cameron-mcwilliams\" aria-label=\"apiculture by cameron mcwilliams permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Apiculture by <em>Cameron McWilliams</em></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://forum.terasology.org/threads/gsoc-2019-apiculture.2267/\">Apiculture</a> is all about bees.\nInspired by the Forestry and ExtraBees mods for Minecraft, <em>Cameron McWilliams</em> raises awareness for sustainability and preserving nature.\nOn the technical side, this project introduces a framework to manage items or blocks used in multiple modules and provides the possibility to simulate genomes.\nAs an extra we get a bee-focused gameplay integration into Josharias‚Äô Survival.</p>\n<h2 id=\"restoration-100-by-e-aakash\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#restoration-100-by-e-aakash\" aria-label=\"restoration 100 by e aakash permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Restoration 100 by <em>E. Aakash</em></h2>\n<p>With ‚Äú<a href=\"https://forum.terasology.org/threads/health-overhaul-gsoc-2019.2263/\">Restoration 100</a>‚Äù, <em>E. Aakash</em> tackles on of the core elements in every game: the player‚Äôs (in-game) health.\nHe realized that no matter if a game mode uses hunger, thirst or health in general, this is always some kind of point pool that can be drained or filled.\nThe target is to provide a well-defined API to other developers that want to use this concept in their modules or game modes.</p>\n<h1 id=\"ux-and-tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ux-and-tools\" aria-label=\"ux and tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>UX and Tools</h1>\n<p>Even the best games will not be played if you don‚Äôt provide good user experience and tooling around them.\nHow to start the game?\nHow to manage versions and updates?\nWhat modules are trending?</p>\n<h2 id=\"module-showcase-website-by-majordwarf\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#module-showcase-website-by-majordwarf\" aria-label=\"module showcase website by majordwarf permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Module Showcase Website by <em>majordwarf</em></h2>\n<p>Terasology‚Äôs basic engine can be extended by a huge amount (201 right now!) of modules.\nKeeping track of them is not the easiest task.\nThis is why <em>majordwarf</em> plans to provide an automated generator for a website, listing all of them.\nThis <a href=\"https://forum.terasology.org/threads/gsoc-proposal-draft-module-showcase-website.2237/\">showcase</a> website will increase discoverability by allowing to filter and search for modules by keywords and categories.</p>\n<h2 id=\"terasology-launcher-40-by-priyadarshi-raj\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#terasology-launcher-40-by-priyadarshi-raj\" aria-label=\"terasology launcher 40 by priyadarshi raj permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Terasology Launcher 4.0 by <em>Priyadarshi Raj</em></h2>\n<p>Our launcher has gone through multiple changes up to now and there‚Äôs another one waiting right ahead: <em>Priydarshi Raj</em> will not only modernize the UI, but also integrate server and game management.\nFurthermore, the launcher will be self-contained in the future without the need to download and set-up additional software such as Java.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.14583333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/3e828/launcher-4.0-mockup.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/e6f2f/launcher-4.0-mockup.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/8b983/launcher-4.0-mockup.webp 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/85811/launcher-4.0-mockup.webp 802w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/8514f/launcher-4.0-mockup.png 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/804b2/launcher-4.0-mockup.png 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/e5715/launcher-4.0-mockup.png 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/5a6dd/launcher-4.0-mockup.png 802w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/ModuleSite/static/5ae71f0a774c4a7c2f8ddde822bfa01c/e5715/launcher-4.0-mockup.png\"\n            alt=\"Launcher 4.0\"\n            title=\"Launcher 4.0\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<h1 id=\"technology\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#technology\" aria-label=\"technology permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Technology</h1>\n<p>Technical parts that reside in the depth of Terasology‚Äôs implementation may not be (immediately) visible to players but are crucial for all the individual gears of the project to interlock.\nThe final two projects are tinkering with things under the hood.</p>\n<h2 id=\"collective-behavior-by-casals\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collective-behavior-by-casals\" aria-label=\"collective behavior by casals permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collective Behavior by <em>casals</em></h2>\n<p><em>casals</em> is our first-ever GSoC PhD student.\nHe plans to bring in <a href=\"https://trello.com/c/9mWFmr17/112-casals-collective-madness\">collective behaviour</a> concepts to be used among multiple actors.\nIn his words: ‚ÄúCollective behavior can be illustrated by a pack of jackals: depending on a certain criteria being satisfied (number of jackals in the pack, number of preys/enemies around), they can either decide to attack or to flee - as a group. But for that to happen, they need to be aware of each other, and to share a behavior.‚Äù</p>\n<h2 id=\"rendering-dag-by-david-s\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rendering-dag-by-david-s\" aria-label=\"rendering dag by david s permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rendering DAG by <em>David S</em></h2>\n<p><em>David S</em> shows ambition to become the new Wizard of Shaderland and Sorcerer of <a href=\"https://trello.com/c/vJr1Qh5I/109-dave2s-dag\">Rendering DAG</a>.\nA directed acyclic graph (DAG) consists of nodes and edges where nodes are features, such as frame-buffers and shaders, and edges denote dependencies between these features.\nThe wizard and sorcerer strides towards softening the dependencies currently hard-coded in the nodes and enabling the expression of magical inter-node dependencies.</p>\n<hr>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>The way students report their progress is determined by the student and their mentors. There is no policy applying to\nall participants, that's why you might find blogs, forum reports for others, or only technical discussion and\ndocumentation for one or another student. We encourage this diversity and are always excited about the format of\nproject documentation.</em></p>\n<p><em>The project summaries and descriptions are partly taken from the student's proposals.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<!-- References -->","timeToRead":5,"excerpt":"It‚Äôs that time of the year again - Google Summer of Code (GSOC) is ahead of us.\nFor the 4th year running we welcome students to become part‚Ä¶","frontmatter":{"title":"GSOC 2019 - An Overview","ddate":"May 29th, 2019","tags":["GSoC"],"author":"Niruandaleth & Skaldarnar","cover":{"publicURL":"/ModuleSite/static/cf3b939df010662b145b4380cb9e76ee/cover.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"l